                        <div class="post-faq-card">
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-4">Is shock loss after hair transplant permanent?</h4>
                            <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">No. Shock loss is almost always temporary. The follicles enter a resting phase due to surgical trauma but retain their ability to regrow. In the vast majority of patients, shock-lost hairs return by months 4–6. Permanent loss of native hairs due to surgical trauma is rare and typically only occurs when the procedure is performed too aggressively or without adequate spacing between grafts.</p>
